## Harness Maintenance

- **Build to delete:** Every skill/hook encodes an assumption about what the model can't do. Periodically stress-test those assumptions. If a skill's failure modes no longer occur, consider removing it.
- **Context budget:** Always-loaded context (CLAUDE.md + rules + MEMORY.md) is limited. Keep it lean. If adding new rules, move lower-frequency reference docs to on-demand skills.
- **Candidates for on-demand conversion:** `rag-usage.md` and `skills-engine.md` are reference docs used infrequently. Consider moving to skills if context budget tightens.
